<div class="page-header">
    <h1><em>Bitcoin</em> vs. The Stock Market</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">What the historical record actually says about buying bitcoin at the worst possible moment &mdash; or every week through every cycle &mdash; versus the same in the S&amp;P 500 or the NASDAQ-100.</p>
</div>

<main class="content-area">
    {% include 'components/tool-framing.njk' %}

    <article class="bvsm-page">

        <p class="prose">If you&rsquo;ve never bought bitcoin and are weighing it against a normal index-fund portfolio, the question that gates the decision is some version of: <em>it&rsquo;s volatile and what if I buy in at exactly the wrong time?</em> The honest answer lives in the historical record. This page anchors on the five scariest scenarios &mdash; lump-sum purchases at the literal top of each bitcoin cycle, including the most recent one in October 2025 &mdash; and walks through what would have happened against the S&amp;P 500 and the NASDAQ-100 over the years that followed. Then it extends the argument forward, using the <a href="/the-power-law.html">Power Law</a> trend to show how long the bitcoin advantage is likely to last for the typical investor&rsquo;s 10-to-15 year horizon.</p>

